The New York Times recently published an essay titled "China's Zero-Covid Policy is a Pandemic Waiting to Happen." Lacking both convincing analysis and scientific evidence, its claim sounds more like the hack prophecy of a bamboozling fortune-teller who later discovers that, in fact, the U.S. is itself stuck in the very same COVID-19 predicament that it had wished upon others. Credits: Editor: Yuan Xin Designer: Cao Yi Senior producer: Wei Wei Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)